  <description type="morphology">Cells of mid-limb lamina (8–)9–12(–14) µm wide (mean 10.5 µm); cells of distal part of leaf sheath with 1–6 papillae on the abaxial surface.  Calyptra often remaining attached to setae at base of capsule.</description>
  <description type="morphology">Almost always with sporo-phytes.  Most often in deciduous forests, on humus in moist, shady calcareous sites, northwards in forested localities, especially along major rivers, and as an adventive in disturbed sites such as lawns, golf courses or cemeteries;</description>
